#: ../../backup.rst:3 940a1bceb22c46f3857edfbe804ddbc2
msgid "Backup and restore"
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:5 9c4dfc9741a74141b8cb3267f72d0d31
msgid ""
"NethSecurity provides a flexible and powerful backup system to save and "
"restore your firewall's configuration settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:7 80f7738ea3a843e9a542c29c53b23e79
msgid ""
"Access the ``Backup & Restore`` page under the ``System`` section, then "
"click on the :guilabel:`Download backup` button. If the machine has a "
"valid Enterprise subscription, the backup is :ref:`automatic "
"<automatic_backup-section>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:10 3b1a582c31bc42ff8e1b681baad251ed
msgid ""
"The backup includes all relevant configuration files and also the list of"
" extra packages installed by the user. The list is saved in the file "
"``/etc/backup/installed_packages.txt``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:14 803d222f1fb54ebc84899fc684560cd1
msgid "Backup encryption"
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:16 d1830c56b07b4054a5d8df4476b7fb6f
msgid ""
"The backup is not encrypted by default. To enable encryption, click on "
"the :guilabel:`Configure passphrase` button and set a strong password. To"
" disable encryption, click on the :guilabel:`Configure passphrase` button"
" and leave the password field empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:20 f3ede11fe6a5402aaafe713d887bf5fa
msgid ""
"If the backup is encrypted and the password is lost, it will no longer be"
" possible to restore the configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:25 7c29f00b3fd9457786c5aff39ecde503
msgid "Restore"
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:27 0615347a272e4e9f893bb9584288ffa5
msgid ""
"The backup can be restored from the the ``Restore`` tab inside the page "
"inside the ``Backup & Restore`` page The user can initiate the restore "
"process by clicking the :guilabel:`Restore backup` button and uploading "
"the backup file. If the machine has a valid Enterprise subscription, the "
"web interface will additionally present a list of backups available from "
"the remote server. If the backup is encrypted, enter the passphrase, and "
"finally, click the :guilabel:`Restore` button to complete the process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:32 e2c8d9dd914d45dd92ff92d9106a72ef
msgid "After the restore the system will be rebooted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:34 8cfcd704ff4c491ea3e39599049c22b8
msgid ""
"If you have installed extra packages, you can restore them by following "
"the instructions in the :ref:`restore_extra_packages-section`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:37 8715c2fa85d549c688b8aa37d1d1c56e
msgid "Automatic backup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:39 ae549156d6194ad4894efb0e182fe309
msgid "Subscription required"
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:41 dcb07a8bdc794cdbbe766c949b32ad05
msgid "This feature is available only if the firewall has a valid subscription."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:43 1a93d932b4a54cd2ab7e100e774ad3cc
msgid ""
"If the machine has a valid :ref:`subscription <subscription-section>`, a "
"scheduled cron job will run every night to perform a backup. This backup "
"is then sent to a remote server over a secure channel. If the backup is "
"encrypted, only the encrypted backup will be sent to the remote server. "
"It is recommended to encrypt the backup to ensure that no one can access "
"the configuration settings stored inside it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:50 97dca0494e364e40b401939f71859597
msgid ""
"Backup without encryption has been deprecated. In the near future, non-"
"encrypted backups will not be sent to the remote server. If you have a "
"valid subscription, please enable encryption to ensure the security of "
"your backup. See also :ref:`backup_encryption-alert` for more "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:55 945c9fba562e4539a4c8e67534ae8475
msgid ""
"The user can click the :guilabel:`Run backup` button: the backup will be "
"stored on a remote server and the user will be able to download it by "
"clicking the :guilabel:`Download` button. Please note that the date of "
"the backup is the server date. The dates displayed in the backup list are"
" based on the time of the server storing the backups, not the time of the"
" firewall that created them. This means the dates might differ depending "
"on time zone differences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:64 8c294bd594c945ec8a8fa570e833181e
msgid "Backup encryption alert"
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:66 fa2fe52ef80d4ad89654fc3abf786422
msgid ""
"Not encrypting the backup is a security risk. If the backup is not "
"encrypted, anyone with access to the backup file can read the "
"configuration settings stored inside it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:69 647cca2f06bb489e812d84f411b6ed57
msgid ""
"Every night a script will check if the backup is encrypted. If the backup"
" is not encrypted, the script will create an alert inside the remote "
"portal my.nethesis.it or my.nethserver.com. To resolve the alert, the "
"user must enable encryption by clicking on the :guilabel:`Configure "
"passphrase` button and setting a strong password. The alert will be "
"resolved automatically during the nightly cron job."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:74 c621cee455d841f6b0dfe1080227a74f
msgid "To disable the alert, access the shell and execute: ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:80 c85c0c7a3c5f4779bdd8fb77505bc304
msgid ""
"Disabling the alert will result in silent failures when the sending of "
"non-encrypted backups is blocked in the future. The administrator will "
"not be notified of these failures, potentially leading to unnoticed "
"backup issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:84 57a8fac4b9024177b3d2eb71675315a1
msgid "Backup customization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:86 beb1cc8b7eb5404c85f3c0c53fbea739
msgid ""
"The backup includes all relevant configuration files. To list the files "
"included in the backup, execute the following command: ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../backup.rst:91 2cd037e7a09341d987ee1c0d7c187ec0
msgid ""
"The backup can be customized by adding files to the backup list. Just add"
" a new line to the file ``/etc/sysupgrade.conf`` with the path of the "
"file to be included in the backup."
msgstr ""

